00:18:33,261 --> 00:18:35,730
Want to tell me about it?

284
00:18:46,107 --> 00:18:49,838
You talked this over
with Crawford. Right?

285
00:18:49,913 --> 00:18:51,211
Right.

286
00:18:51,279 --> 00:18:52,874
How did that go?

287
00:18:52,950 --> 00:18:54,915
It didn't change anything.

288
00:18:54,986 --> 00:18:56,884
What needed changing?

289
00:18:56,951 --> 00:19:01,015
I'd like to be more in control.

290
00:19:01,092 --> 00:19:02,719
Why?

291
00:19:02,790 --> 00:19:05,588
So people can quit
worrying about me.

292
00:19:06,663 --> 00:19:08,856
Well. I'll tell you something.

293
00:19:08,932 --> 00:19:11,865
I'll be straight with you. Okay?

294
00:19:11,933 --> 00:19:14,663
I'm not big on control.

295
00:19:16,605 --> 00:19:18,575
But it's your money.

296
00:19:18,643 --> 00:19:20,508
So to speak.

297
00:19:21,644 --> 00:19:23,009
So to speak.

298
00:19:24,212 --> 00:19:26,284
Okay.

299
00:19:30,788 --> 00:19:33,382
How's Tuesdays...

300
00:19:33,457 --> 00:19:35,391
and Fridays. Same time?

301
00:19:35,459 --> 00:19:37,617
Twice a week?

302
00:19:37,692 --> 00:19:40,630
Well. Control's a tough nut.

303
00:19:40,698 --> 00:19:43,461
I've got swim practice every night.

304
00:19:44,969 --> 00:19:46,903
Well. That's a problem.

305
00:19:46,971 --> 00:19:50,372
How do we solve that?

306
00:19:51,409 --> 00:19:54,136
Guess I'll skip practice
twice a week.

307
00:19:54,211 --> 00:19:55,644
Well. It's up to you.

308
00:19:55,711 --> 00:19:58,144
I don't like being here.

309
00:19:58,212 --> 00:20:00,682
I don't like it at all.

310
00:20:02,116 --> 00:20:03,913
Mm-hmm.

311
00:20:06,123 --> 00:20:10,615
I saw Mort Swain.
His sister died.

312
00:20:10,692 --> 00:20:12,959
The one from Idaho?

313
00:20:13,028 --> 00:20:15,555
The one with the restaurant.

314
00:20:15,633 --> 00:20:17,624
She died in Idaho?

315
00:20:17,701 --> 00:20:19,169
I guess so.

316
00:20:20,237 --> 00:20:21,567
Why?

317
00:20:21,636 --> 00:20:24,799
You said she was always traveling.

318
00:20:24,875 --> 00:20:26,307
I don't know.

319
00:20:26,375 --> 00:20:28,173
Maybe in Idaho.

320
00:20:28,242 --> 00:20:30,509
Maybe Kansas City.

321
00:20:36,987 --> 00:20:39,421
I went to see Dr. Berger.

322
00:20:39,490 --> 00:20:41,423
Berger?

323
00:20:41,490 --> 00:20:43,184
Yeah.

324
00:20:43,259 --> 00:20:44,921
You didn't say anything. Good!

325
00:20:44,992 --> 00:20:46,586
I went today.

326
00:20:46,663 --> 00:20:49,596
I didn't know
you made an appointment.

327
00:20:49,664 --> 00:20:50,929
How was it?

328
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:52,662
It's a lot of money.

329
00:20:52,737 --> 00:20:54,671
It's okay.

330
00:20:54,739 --> 00:20:57,933
It's $50 an hour.
Twice a week.

331
00:20:58,008 --> 00:21:00,942
It's okay.
It is necessary.

332
00:21:01,009 --> 00:21:03,775
What did you talk about?

333
00:21:03,846 --> 00:21:05,039
Not much.

334
00:21:05,115 --> 00:21:06,548
What about your schedule?

335
00:21:06,615 --> 00:21:10,278
Well. It'll cut
into swim practice.

336
00:21:10,354 --> 00:21:12,444
Where's his office?

337
00:21:12,520 --> 00:21:13,953
Highland Park.

338
00:21:17,928 --> 00:21:19,894
Head straight!

339
00:21:19,961 --> 00:21:23,400
I don't want to tell you again.

340
00:21:25,134 --> 00:21:27,730
This is what I see.

341
00:21:27,805 --> 00:21:31,067
I see you yawning
and you coming late.

342
00:21:31,142 --> 00:21:33,872
I don't see you having fun.

343
00:21:33,942 --> 00:21:36,740
Are you getting enough sleep?

344
00:21:36,814 --> 00:21:38,211
Yeah.

345
00:21:39,750 --> 00:21:41,240
Are you having fun?

346
00:21:41,317 --> 00:21:42,577
Fun?

347
00:21:42,653 --> 00:21:46,180
There's no point
if you're not having fun.

348
00:21:46,257 --> 00:21:48,191
Yeah. I guess so.

349
00:21:48,259 --> 00:21:49,655
You guess so.

350
00:21:52,229 --> 00:21:54,220
Are you on medication?

351
00:21:54,298 --> 00:21:55,694
Tranquilizers?

352
00:21:55,766 --> 00:21:56,991
Anything?

353
00:21:57,067 --> 00:21:59,592
No. No. Sir.

354
00:21:59,670 --> 00:22:02,261
Did I ask you
if they gave you shock?

355
00:22:02,336 --> 00:22:03,826
Yeah.

356
00:22:03,905 --> 00:22:05,432
Yeah what?

357
00:22:05,509 --> 00:22:07,337
Yeah. You asked me.

358
00:22:07,411 --> 00:22:08,844
Yeah. They did.

359
00:22:11,115 --> 00:22:13,015
Don't look at us. Lazenby.

360
00:22:13,083 --> 00:22:15,017
Get in the water!

361
00:22:19,923 --> 00:22:23,257
I'm no doctor. Jarrett.

362
00:22:23,326 --> 00:22:27,057
I wouldn't let them
put electricity in my head.

363
00:22:29,163 --> 00:22:31,097
He drives me nuts!

364
00:22:31,165 --> 00:22:33,827
Everybody drives you nuts.

365
00:22:36,140 --> 00:22:38,074
Don and Fenetch looked good.

366
00:22:38,142 --> 00:22:40,007
They looked very good.

367
00:22:40,076 --> 00:22:43,009
Is he giving you a hard time?

368
00:22:43,077 --> 00:22:45,011
Want a clarinet?

369
00:22:45,082 --> 00:22:47,016
Van Buren wants a clarinet.

370
00:22:47,084 --> 00:22:48,517
Who's selling it?

371
00:22:48,586 --> 00:22:50,519
My brother.
He needs a motorcycle.

372
00:22:50,586 --> 00:22:53,056
You stand behind me
in the choir.

373
00:22:53,123 --> 00:22:55,717
Oh. I do?
Is that you?

374
00:22:55,790 --> 00:22:58,159
You have a lot of energy.

375
00:22:58,229 --> 00:22:59,250
I do?

376
00:22:59,327 --> 00:23:01,057
I mean. That's good.

377
00:23:01,131 --> 00:23:03,065
My name's Jeannine Pratt.

378
00:23:03,133 --> 00:23:04,566
Nice. Hi.

379
00:23:04,634 --> 00:23:06,067
You're Conrad Jarrett.

380
00:23:06,134 --> 00:23:07,296
Right.

381
00:23:09,471 --> 00:23:11,065
Yeah. Um. Bye.

382
00:23:11,141 --> 00:23:12,574
Bye-bye.

383
00:23:13,644 --> 00:23:16,576
"You've got a lot of energy."

384
00:23:19,981 --> 00:23:21,576
[Children]
Trick or treat!

385
00:23:21,652 --> 00:23:25,086
You're the scariest
ghost I've ever seen!

386
00:23:25,153 --> 00:23:26,586
You look wonderful.

387
00:23:26,654 --> 00:23:28,588
Thank you.

388
00:23:28,659 --> 00:23:29,588
There you go.

389
00:23:29,660 --> 00:23:31,093
Be careful.

390
00:23:31,161 --> 00:23:33,095
Thank you.
Good-bye.

391
00:23:34,163 --> 00:23:36,596
The Cabots.
Julie's first time.

392
00:23:36,664 --> 00:23:38,601
She's so cute!

393
00:23:40,434 --> 00:23:42,997
Ha! Ha! Ha! Ha!

394
00:23:43,073 --> 00:23:46,269
Know what I've been thinking?

395
00:23:46,343 --> 00:23:48,277
That Christmas in London...

396
00:23:48,345 --> 00:23:51,778
would be like something
out of Dickens.

397
00:23:51,846 --> 00:23:54,280
We've never done that before.

398
00:23:54,351 --> 00:23:58,788
Maybe we shouldn't plan
to go away right now.

399
00:23:58,855 --> 00:24:00,788
We talked about it.

400
00:24:00,855 --> 00:24:02,789
We decided on that.

401
00:24:02,857 --> 00:24:04,794
Yeah. I know that.

402
00:24:04,862 --> 00:24:07,797
But the timing
doesn't seem right.

403
00:24:07,865 --> 00:24:10,798
We've always gone away
at Christmas.

404
00:24:10,865 --> 00:24:13,528
It'd be good for him. Too.

405
00:24:13,604 --> 00:24:16,038
Let's get back to normal.

406
00:24:16,105 --> 00:24:18,799
He's just started
with this doctor.

407
00:24:18,875 --> 00:24:20,807
He'll miss three weeks.

408
00:24:20,875 --> 00:24:22,308
Why interrupt it?

409
00:24:22,376 --> 00:24:25,314
Because I want to get away.

410
00:24:25,382 --> 00:24:28,317
I think we should.
It's important.

411
00:24:28,384 --> 00:24:32,819
Not if he doesn't
go through with this now.

412
00:24:32,890 --> 00:24:35,324
He might change his mind.

413
00:24:35,392 --> 00:24:37,826
If he changes his mind...

414
00:24:37,894 --> 00:24:40,087
it wasn't right for him.

415
00:24:40,163 --> 00:24:42,428
Does he want to go?

416
00:24:42,499 --> 00:24:45,432
He doesn't know what he wants.

417
00:26:52,626 --> 00:26:54,392
Ahh!

418
00:26:54,462 --> 00:26:56,160
Don't do that!

419
00:26:56,230 --> 00:26:57,663
I'm sorry.

420
00:26:57,732 --> 00:27:00,670
I didn't think you were here.

421
00:27:00,738 --> 00:27:02,672
I just got in.

422
00:27:02,740 --> 00:27:04,673
No golf today.
Too cold.

423
00:27:04,740 --> 00:27:06,173
How was golf?

424
00:27:06,240 --> 00:27:07,673
I didn't play.

425
00:27:07,742 --> 00:27:09,178
It's colder today.

426
00:27:09,246 --> 00:27:12,682
I mean. For the year.
It's colder.

427
00:27:13,884 --> 00:27:15,317
Weren't you swimming?

428
00:27:15,384 --> 00:27:17,817
Yeah. Sorry I scared you.

429
00:27:17,885 --> 00:27:19,318
How'd it go?

430
00:27:19,386 --> 00:27:21,323
Good. I swam well.

431
00:27:21,391 --> 00:27:22,323
Good.

432
00:27:22,392 --> 00:27:25,826
I could swim the 50 if my...

433
00:27:25,894 --> 00:27:27,827
my timing got better.

434
00:27:27,895 --> 00:27:29,832
I'm a little off.

435
00:27:29,900 --> 00:27:32,334
You must work at that.

436
00:27:32,402 --> 00:27:33,334
Yeah.

437
00:27:33,403 --> 00:27:37,441
I got 74 on a Trig quiz.

438
00:27:37,574 --> 00:27:38,971
74?

439
00:27:39,039 --> 00:27:41,977
Gee. I was awful at Trig.

440
00:27:42,045 --> 00:27:43,478
Oh. Yeah? Did you...

441
00:27:43,547 --> 00:27:45,708
You took Trig?

442
00:27:48,018 --> 00:27:49,644
Wait a minute.

443
00:27:52,055 --> 00:27:53,613
Did I take Trig?

444
00:27:57,294 --> 00:28:00,957
I bought you two shirts.
They're on your bed.

445
00:28:04,731 --> 00:28:06,565
Who'll be there?

446
00:28:06,634 --> 00:28:10,663
Well. The Murrays.
The Gunthers. And the Caines.

447
00:28:10,740 --> 00:28:13,538
Let's go to the movies instead.

448
00:28:13,607 --> 00:28:16,269
Don't be negative.

449
00:28:16,346 --> 00:28:18,678
That's not negative.
That's unpredictable.

450
00:28:18,748 --> 00:28:21,077
Let's go to the movies.

451
00:28:21,151 --> 00:28:22,548
Okay.

452
00:28:22,616 --> 00:28:24,174
Really?

453
00:28:24,251 --> 00:28:27,018
Okay. Yeah.
Come on. Let's go.

454
00:28:27,087 --> 00:28:28,520
What's our excuse?

455
00:28:29,593 --> 00:28:33,356
Beth wanted to go
to the movies.

456
00:28:33,430 --> 00:28:34,519
Good.

457
00:28:34,596 --> 00:28:36,122
Very good.

458
00:28:41,702 --> 00:28:43,636
All right now. Smile.

459
00:28:43,707 --> 00:28:46,574
Remember. Not too many martinis.

460
00:28:51,211 --> 00:28:54,650
Will you put that
with the others?

461
00:28:54,718 --> 00:28:56,652
Look. We're in time.

462
00:28:56,720 --> 00:28:58,153
Look who's here!

463
00:28:58,221 --> 00:29:02,154
Three blocks away
and the last to arrive.

464
00:29:02,222 --> 00:29:03,655
Come on in.

465
00:29:03,727 --> 00:29:06,161
Happy birthday!
You look wonderful.

466
00:29:06,229 --> 00:29:07,662
Is that new?

467
00:29:07,730 --> 00:29:10,663
Yes. It is.
Do you like it?

468
00:29:11,732 --> 00:29:13,097
You did the mousse?

469
00:29:13,169 --> 00:29:14,463
It turned out well?

470
00:29:14,538 --> 00:29:17,096
Hey. Partner.
How are you?

471
00:29:17,173 --> 00:29:18,834
Hi there.

472
00:29:18,909 --> 00:29:20,807
Hi. Beth.

473
00:29:20,875 --> 00:29:22,401
Good to see you.

474
00:29:22,479 --> 00:29:23,807
Borrow the money.

475
00:29:23,880 --> 00:29:25,313
I'll go public.

476
00:29:25,382 --> 00:29:29,478
I wouldn't do it now
because the market's low.

477
00:29:29,553 --> 00:29:31,316
Your hair looks wonderful.

478
00:29:31,385 --> 00:29:33,913
It's shorter. You like it?

479
00:29:33,990 --> 00:29:37,585
I said.
"Please put out your cigar."

480
00:29:37,661 --> 00:29:41,461
He says. "Huh?
I don't have another one."

481
00:29:42,663 --> 00:29:45,097
Good to see you!

482
00:29:45,165 --> 00:29:47,432
You look beautiful. As ever.

483
00:29:47,501 --> 00:29:48,934
In school...

484
00:29:49,005 --> 00:29:54,102
they think they've got
to walk on the edge of danger.

485
00:29:54,174 --> 00:29:56,269
What are these hushed tones?

486
00:29:56,346 --> 00:29:58,403
He told the funniest joke!

487
00:30:00,682 --> 00:30:03,084
I'm not talking to you.

488
00:30:03,153 --> 00:30:04,450
Why?

489
00:30:04,519 --> 00:30:08,218
I have my fingers crossed
on this merger.

490
00:30:08,288 --> 00:30:09,451
Let's have lunch.

491
00:30:09,526 --> 00:30:11,788
I don't know my schedule.

492
00:30:11,861 --> 00:30:14,125
I'm free most days.

493
00:30:14,194 --> 00:30:16,788
Bob McLean's leaving
Coles and Johnson.

494
00:30:16,865 --> 00:30:18,798
Where is he going?

495
00:30:18,865 --> 00:30:20,836
He doesn't know.

496
00:30:20,903 --> 00:30:22,132
Jesus.

497
00:30:22,202 --> 00:30:23,672
No. You didn't.

498
00:30:23,740 --> 00:30:27,073
Isn't he the meanest man
you've met?

499
00:30:27,143 --> 00:30:29,441
When a ball is in play.

500
00:30:29,509 --> 00:30:33,471
If a player or caddy
accidentally move it...

501
00:30:33,548 --> 00:30:35,674
#Jolly good fellow #

502
00:30:35,750 --> 00:30:38,220
# For he's a jolly good fellow ##

503
00:30:40,323 --> 00:30:43,486
# Won't regret. Can't forget #

504
00:30:43,557 --> 00:30:45,892
# What we did #

505
00:30:45,961 --> 00:30:48,487
# For #

506
00:30:48,565 --> 00:30:53,332
# Love ##

507
00:30:57,007 --> 00:31:00,170
Hi. Annie. What's your boy up to?

508
00:31:00,240 --> 00:31:01,673
Oh. Who knows?

509
00:31:01,742 --> 00:31:03,508
How's Conrad doing?

510
00:31:03,577 --> 00:31:05,511
He's great. Just great.

511
00:31:05,582 --> 00:31:09,778
I asked Donald.
He says they haven't talked much.

512
00:31:09,853 --> 00:31:12,515
I said maybe he's self-conscious.

513
00:31:12,586 --> 00:31:13,519
Oh!

514
00:31:16,923 --> 00:31:19,519
No. No. No.

515
00:31:19,596 --> 00:31:21,528
No. He's...

516
00:31:21,596 --> 00:31:25,125
There's a doctor
in Highland Park...

517
00:31:25,201 --> 00:31:27,530
that he sees twice a week.

518
00:31:27,604 --> 00:31:29,865
He's great. Just great.

519
00:31:29,939 --> 00:31:33,102
Is he still having some problems?

520
00:31:33,173 --> 00:31:35,038
No. Nothing like that.

521
00:31:35,111 --> 00:31:37,545
Just somebody to talk to...

522
00:31:37,614 --> 00:31:39,980
to polish off the rough edges.

523
00:31:40,048 --> 00:31:41,605
How are you. Darling?

524
00:31:41,682 --> 00:31:44,116
Is he falling asleep on you?

525
00:31:44,184 --> 00:31:45,913
Nah. He's great.

526
00:31:47,190 --> 00:31:48,987
[Mimicking "Mr. Wonderful"]
# Mr. Great. That's me #

527
00:31:54,064 --> 00:31:54,996
Hey.

528
00:31:56,700 --> 00:31:58,790
You drank too much.

529
00:31:58,865 --> 00:32:00,298
I'm not drunk.

530
00:32:00,367 --> 00:32:03,962
Why did you tell Annie
about Conrad's psychiatrist?

531
00:32:04,038 --> 00:32:05,471
Why not?

532
00:32:05,539 --> 00:32:08,634
People don't hear
that thing easily.

533
00:32:08,711 --> 00:32:12,145
For most people.
It's a status symbol.

534
00:32:12,212 --> 00:32:14,646
Well. Your blurting it out...

535
00:32:14,718 --> 00:32:16,652
was a violation of privacy.

536
00:32:16,720 --> 00:32:18,153
Whose privacy?

537
00:32:18,221 --> 00:32:20,049
The family's privacy!

538
00:32:20,123 --> 00:32:23,057
I think it is
a very private matter.

539
00:32:30,798 --> 00:32:33,064
I tell you my dreams?

540
00:32:33,134 --> 00:32:35,567
I don't believe in dreams.

541
00:32:35,635 --> 00:32:39,096
What kind of
a psychiatrist are you?

542
00:32:39,173 --> 00:32:41,575
What's happening?

543
00:32:42,711 --> 00:32:44,009
What's going on?

544
00:32:44,077 --> 00:32:46,011
I just feel...

545
00:32:46,082 --> 00:32:48,073
I feel so...

546
00:32:50,183 --> 00:32:51,115
What?

547
00:32:51,184 --> 00:32:52,981
Jumpy. I don't know.

548
00:32:53,056 --> 00:32:54,546
Look. Kiddo...

549
00:32:55,625 --> 00:32:57,217
I lied.

550
00:32:58,294 --> 00:33:00,228
I believe in dreams.

551
00:33:00,296 --> 00:33:04,230
Sometimes I want to know
what's happening when you're awake.

552
00:33:04,298 --> 00:33:06,632
Something's making you nervous.

553
00:33:06,701 --> 00:33:09,171
Maybe I need a tranquilizer.

554
00:33:09,239 --> 00:33:10,328
Tranquilizer?

555
00:33:10,403 --> 00:33:12,701
What do you think?

556
00:33:12,776 --> 00:33:16,231
You look like something
out of The Body Snatchers.

557
00:33:16,309 --> 00:33:19,576
It's not my impression
that you need a tranquilizer.

558
00:33:21,481 --> 00:33:23,111
What is this?

559
00:33:23,183 --> 00:33:24,913
A clock.

560
00:33:24,988 --> 00:33:28,423
You can tell the time.
But I can't.

561
00:33:28,490 --> 00:33:31,616
So you know when
the hour's up?

562
00:33:31,692 --> 00:33:32,953
Right.

563
00:33:33,028 --> 00:33:34,653
50. 55 minutes?

