01:04:40,693 --> 01:04:43,184
Hi. What do you think?

1125
01:04:45,364 --> 01:04:47,630
It's very nice.

1126
01:04:49,168 --> 01:04:50,601
What is wrong?

1127
01:04:50,670 --> 01:04:52,103
Ask him what's wrong.

1128
01:04:52,172 --> 01:04:55,902
Maybe you won't have to
hear it from Carol Lazenby.

1129
01:04:55,976 --> 01:04:57,375
Hear what?

1130
01:05:01,081 --> 01:05:03,547
I quit the swim team.

1131
01:05:03,617 --> 01:05:05,777
Carol thought I knew.

1132
01:05:05,853 --> 01:05:08,822
It happened over a month ago.

1133
01:05:08,889 --> 01:05:10,288
Quit? When?

1134
01:05:11,358 --> 01:05:14,018
Where have you been every night?

1135
01:05:14,094 --> 01:05:16,027
Nowhere.
The library mostly.

1136
01:05:16,096 --> 01:05:18,826
I didn't think it mattered.

1137
01:05:18,898 --> 01:05:21,333
That was meant for me.

1138
01:05:21,402 --> 01:05:24,632
It's important to hurt me. Right?

1139
01:05:24,704 --> 01:05:26,605
You have that backwards.

1140
01:05:26,672 --> 01:05:30,632
Do I embarrass you
in front of friends?

1141
01:05:30,710 --> 01:05:34,704
"Poor Beth believes
every lie her son tells."

1142
01:05:34,782 --> 01:05:36,271
I didn't lie.

1143
01:05:36,349 --> 01:05:40,376
You did when
you came home at 6:30!

1144
01:05:40,454 --> 01:05:44,514
If the lying's starting again.
I can't stand it!

1145
01:05:44,590 --> 01:05:46,855
Then go to Europe!

1146
01:05:46,927 --> 01:05:52,297
She only gives a fuck because
someone else knew about it first!

1147
01:05:52,364 --> 01:05:55,699
She never came
to the hospital...

1148
01:05:55,768 --> 01:05:59,295
because she's busy going
to goddamn Spain and Portugal!

1149
01:05:59,373 --> 01:06:03,867
She doesn't care if I'm hung up
by the balls out there.

1150
01:06:03,943 --> 01:06:06,742
They may talk like this
at the hospital...

1151
01:06:06,813 --> 01:06:09,338
but we're not at the hospital.

1152
01:06:09,416 --> 01:06:11,849
You never came to the hospital!

1153
01:06:11,918 --> 01:06:14,614
She had the flu
and couldn't come inside.

1154
01:06:14,688 --> 01:06:17,657
She would've visited Buck
in the hospital!

1155
01:06:17,724 --> 01:06:20,626
Buck never would've been
in the hospital!

1156
01:06:20,693 --> 01:06:22,355
That is enough!

1157
01:06:22,429 --> 01:06:25,159
I won't do it again.

1158
01:06:25,231 --> 01:06:27,826
What in hell has happened?

1159
01:06:27,900 --> 01:06:30,425
Somebody better go up there.

1160
01:06:30,503 --> 01:06:32,869
He walks all over us...

1161
01:06:32,940 --> 01:06:36,103
then you apologize to him.

1162
01:06:36,175 --> 01:06:37,905
You've been apologizing to him...

1163
01:06:37,978 --> 01:06:41,072
since he returned from the hospital!

1164
01:06:41,148 --> 01:06:44,606
I'm trying to
goddamn understand him!

1165
01:06:44,684 --> 01:06:46,311
Don't talk to me...

1166
01:06:46,385 --> 01:06:48,945
the way he talks to you.

1167
01:06:49,021 --> 01:06:51,489
Let's not fight. Okay?

1168
01:06:51,556 --> 01:06:53,114
No fighting. Okay?

1169
01:06:53,193 --> 01:06:55,092
Please.

1170
01:06:55,161 --> 01:06:56,789
Let's go upstairs.

1171
01:07:15,916 --> 01:07:18,315
I want to talk to you.

1172
01:07:18,385 --> 01:07:20,945
I didn't mean any of it.

1173
01:07:21,021 --> 01:07:23,215
Please don't be mad.

1174
01:07:23,289 --> 01:07:26,157
I'm trying to
understand what happened.

1175
01:07:26,226 --> 01:07:28,717
I don't know what happened.

1176
01:07:28,795 --> 01:07:30,730
I didn't mean it.

1177
01:07:30,797 --> 01:07:33,960
Tell her I'm sorry. Will you?

1178
01:07:34,034 --> 01:07:35,126
Why don't you?

1179
01:07:35,202 --> 01:07:36,965
God. I can't!

1180
01:07:37,036 --> 01:07:39,505
I can't talk to her!

1181
01:07:39,572 --> 01:07:41,039
Why not?

1182
01:07:41,108 --> 01:07:43,099
It doesn't change anything.

1183
01:07:43,177 --> 01:07:47,704
It doesn't change
the way she looks at me.

1184
01:07:47,780 --> 01:07:51,806
She was hurt because
you quit the team.

1185
01:07:51,885 --> 01:07:54,353
I don't mean just now.

1186
01:07:54,420 --> 01:07:56,911
I don't mean just today.

1187
01:07:56,989 --> 01:07:58,980
Explain it to me.

1188
01:07:59,059 --> 01:08:02,050
I can't. You don't see things.

1189
01:08:02,128 --> 01:08:03,594
What things?

1190
01:08:03,663 --> 01:08:05,291
What things?

1191
01:08:05,364 --> 01:08:08,356
I want you to tell me.

1192
01:08:08,434 --> 01:08:11,527
Can't you see she hates me?

1193
01:08:11,603 --> 01:08:13,505
She doesn't hate you.

1194
01:08:13,572 --> 01:08:16,099
You're right.
She doesn't.

1195
01:08:16,176 --> 01:08:18,167
Please leave me alone.

1196
01:08:30,988 --> 01:08:34,448
Do you think Dr. Berger's helping you?

1197
01:08:34,528 --> 01:08:36,393
It's not his fault.

1198
01:08:42,536 --> 01:08:45,505
I'll be downstairs if you need me.

1199
01:08:49,943 --> 01:08:53,935
Tuesday everything was hunky-dory.

1200
01:08:54,014 --> 01:08:55,447
You're the doctor.

1201
01:08:58,452 --> 01:09:01,386
Don't take refuge
in one-liners. Okay?

1202
01:09:01,453 --> 01:09:03,389
Because that pisses me off.

1203
01:09:03,457 --> 01:09:05,890
Okay. Okay.

1204
01:09:05,957 --> 01:09:07,390
Everything was fine...

1205
01:09:07,461 --> 01:09:10,395
till you had the fight
with your mother?

1206
01:09:10,462 --> 01:09:11,895
I don't blame her.

1207
01:09:11,965 --> 01:09:14,399
She's got her reasons.
It's impossible...

1208
01:09:14,466 --> 01:09:16,402
after all the shit I've pulled.

1209
01:09:16,470 --> 01:09:18,404
What shit have you pulled?

1210
01:09:20,974 --> 01:09:23,340
I'm talking about proportion.

1211
01:09:23,408 --> 01:09:25,310
Now. What shit?

1212
01:09:28,381 --> 01:09:32,341
You can find one example.

1213
01:09:32,417 --> 01:09:34,353
Don't say you tried suicide.

1214
01:09:34,421 --> 01:09:36,354
What have you done lately?

1215
01:09:36,421 --> 01:09:40,051
I'll never be forgiven for that.

1216
01:09:40,127 --> 01:09:41,617
Never.

1217
01:09:41,694 --> 01:09:45,791
You can't get out
the blood in her towels...

1218
01:09:45,863 --> 01:09:47,890
and in her rug.

1219
01:09:47,966 --> 01:09:50,493
Everything
had to be pitched.

1220
01:09:50,569 --> 01:09:54,162
The bathroom tile
had to be regrouted.

1221
01:09:54,238 --> 01:09:55,970
She fired the maid...

1222
01:09:56,042 --> 01:09:58,876
because she couldn't dust right.

1223
01:09:58,944 --> 01:10:01,470
If you think I'll forgive...

1224
01:10:01,546 --> 01:10:03,037
she's gonna forgive me...

1225
01:10:11,055 --> 01:10:12,216
What?

1226
01:10:32,310 --> 01:10:36,078
I think I just figured
something out.

1227
01:10:36,149 --> 01:10:37,613
What?

1228
01:10:39,219 --> 01:10:41,653
Who it is who can't forgive who.

1229
01:10:46,926 --> 01:10:50,363
[Berger]
A real problem has a real solution.

1230
01:10:50,430 --> 01:10:52,421
[Conrad]
I've heard this before.

1231
01:10:52,497 --> 01:10:55,524
Doesn't make it any less true.

1232
01:10:55,600 --> 01:10:57,091
I'm so tired.

1233
01:10:57,171 --> 01:11:00,197
That's some secret
you've been keeping.

1234
01:11:00,274 --> 01:11:03,300
So what do I do now?

1235
01:11:04,912 --> 01:11:06,935
Recognize her limitations.

1236
01:11:08,046 --> 01:11:10,537
Like she can't love me.

1237
01:11:10,617 --> 01:11:14,551
No. Like she can't
love you enough.

1238
01:11:14,621 --> 01:11:17,783
Don't blame her
for not loving you...

1239
01:11:17,858 --> 01:11:19,849
more than she's able.

1240
01:11:19,926 --> 01:11:21,917
She loves my father.

1241
01:11:21,993 --> 01:11:23,984
She loved my brother.

1242
01:11:24,064 --> 01:11:25,725
It's me.

1243
01:11:25,796 --> 01:11:28,893
We're back to
the rotten kid routine.

1244
01:11:28,969 --> 01:11:32,801
She can't love you
because you're unlovable.

1245
01:11:32,872 --> 01:11:35,966
How come your Dad loves you?

1246
01:11:36,042 --> 01:11:38,511
He feels responsible.

1247
01:11:38,578 --> 01:11:40,569
Besides. He loves everybody.

1248
01:11:40,645 --> 01:11:43,171
The guy's got no taste.

1249
01:11:43,250 --> 01:11:46,242
He loves you. But he's wrong.

1250
01:11:46,319 --> 01:11:47,787
Look...

1251
01:11:47,854 --> 01:11:50,845
maybe she can't express it...

1252
01:11:50,921 --> 01:11:52,890
the way you'd like.

1253
01:11:52,960 --> 01:11:56,225
Maybe she's afraid
to show her feelings.

1254
01:11:56,296 --> 01:11:58,524
What do you mean?

1255
01:11:58,599 --> 01:12:00,930
There's someone
besides your mother...

1256
01:12:01,001 --> 01:12:02,591
you've got to forgive.

1257
01:12:02,667 --> 01:12:04,430
You mean me?

1258
01:12:06,305 --> 01:12:08,831
For trying to off myself?

1259
01:12:10,978 --> 01:12:12,969
Don't stare.
What for?

1260
01:12:13,046 --> 01:12:16,979
Why don't you let yourself
off the hook?

1261
01:12:17,050 --> 01:12:20,076
What did I do?

1262
01:12:20,153 --> 01:12:21,743
What did I do?

1263
01:12:21,822 --> 01:12:23,287
We'll talk Thursday.

1264
01:12:23,354 --> 01:12:24,287
Come on!

1265
01:12:24,358 --> 01:12:26,087
Time's up.

1266
01:12:26,158 --> 01:12:28,591
What did I do?

1267
01:12:28,662 --> 01:12:30,060
You know the rules.

1268
01:12:30,130 --> 01:12:31,618
What rules?

1269
01:12:31,698 --> 01:12:33,393
Think about it.

1270
01:12:33,466 --> 01:12:35,059
Just think about it.

1271
01:12:38,203 --> 01:12:39,466
Jesus!

1272
01:12:43,676 --> 01:12:46,237
Say. After going to a new high...

1273
01:12:46,313 --> 01:12:48,679
it falls to 1121/4...

1274
01:12:48,747 --> 01:12:51,738
and then rallies on good volume.

1275
01:12:51,818 --> 01:12:54,252
I order to buy 4.000.

1276
01:12:54,319 --> 01:12:58,587
If I get the 4.000 at 1133/4.
I know something's wrong.

1277
01:12:58,658 --> 01:13:02,595
But suppose I order
to buy the 4.000 shares...

1278
01:13:02,662 --> 01:13:05,529
and I plug in at 1133/4...

1279
01:13:05,599 --> 01:13:09,466
I get 2.000 at 114.
500 at 1141/4...

1280
01:13:09,536 --> 01:13:12,403
and the rest on the way up.

1281
01:13:12,470 --> 01:13:14,497
Then I know I'm right.

1282
01:13:14,573 --> 01:13:17,439
I'm going to peel off here.

1283
01:13:17,511 --> 01:13:19,444
See you later.

1284
01:13:24,184 --> 01:13:26,810
[Voice Echoing]
Suppose the order to buy...

1285
01:13:26,886 --> 01:13:28,819
[Beth's Voice]
You let him walk all over us...

1286
01:13:28,889 --> 01:13:30,149
and you apologize.

1287
01:13:30,220 --> 01:13:31,884
[Man's Voice]
500 at 114...

1288
01:13:31,957 --> 01:13:33,926
[Conrad's Voice]
Dad, you don't see things.

1289
01:13:33,993 --> 01:13:35,791
[Beth]
You've been apologizing...

1290
01:13:35,862 --> 01:13:39,161
since he returned from the hospital.

1291
01:13:39,229 --> 01:13:41,166
Tell her to stop it!

1292
01:13:41,234 --> 01:13:44,292
Buck never would've
been in the hospital!

1293
01:13:44,371 --> 01:13:45,702
She hates me!

1294
01:14:07,993 --> 01:14:09,724
I want to be clear.

1295
01:14:09,796 --> 01:14:11,591
That's good.

1296
01:14:13,500 --> 01:14:18,095
In the car.
I was thinking. "be clear."

1297
01:14:21,506 --> 01:14:23,942
I suppose that's what
psychiatry's about.

1298
01:14:24,011 --> 01:14:26,411
Being precise and clear.

1299
01:14:26,479 --> 01:14:28,448
And honest, of course.

1300
01:14:29,850 --> 01:14:33,809
I'm not a great believer
in psychiatry.

1301
01:14:33,886 --> 01:14:35,613
Okay.

1302
01:14:35,689 --> 01:14:39,318
What happens here
is between you and him...

1303
01:14:39,393 --> 01:14:41,384
and I respect that.

1304
01:14:41,461 --> 01:14:43,895
He's better.
I can see that.

1305
01:14:43,962 --> 01:14:46,761
I just don't believe in psychiatry...

1306
01:14:46,832 --> 01:14:50,095
as a panacea for everybody.

1307
01:14:50,170 --> 01:14:51,636
Neither do I.

1308
01:14:54,608 --> 01:14:59,170
I wish I knew what
I was doing here.

1309
01:14:59,246 --> 01:15:03,203
You said you could shed
some light on some things.

1310
01:15:03,283 --> 01:15:06,844
I meant in terms of Conrad.

1311
01:15:06,920 --> 01:15:09,411
I knew something was wrong...

1312
01:15:09,488 --> 01:15:11,979
even before he tried suicide.

1313
01:15:12,059 --> 01:15:14,027
But I thought that...

1314
01:15:15,127 --> 01:15:18,118
It's clear that he's very smart.

1315
01:15:18,198 --> 01:15:21,189
He's always been
an "A" student.

1316
01:15:21,268 --> 01:15:23,759
Naturally. I thought
intelligent people...

1317
01:15:23,837 --> 01:15:26,237
could work out their problems.

1318
01:15:26,305 --> 01:15:28,899
But you still feel responsible?

1319
01:15:28,975 --> 01:15:31,000
Yeah, sure I do.

1320
01:15:31,078 --> 01:15:33,103
It's hard not to.

1321
01:15:33,180 --> 01:15:37,742
It was just luck that
I happened to be there...

1322
01:15:37,818 --> 01:15:39,786
when he tried it.

1323
01:15:39,853 --> 01:15:42,546
We both could've been away.

1324
01:15:42,622 --> 01:15:46,613
You think of yourself
as a lucky man?

1325
01:15:46,693 --> 01:15:48,180
No. No. No.

1326
01:15:48,261 --> 01:15:53,287
I used to think that
I was a lucky person...

1327
01:15:53,363 --> 01:15:55,027
before the accident.

1328
01:15:59,706 --> 01:16:02,729
I guess the whole of life...

1329
01:16:02,809 --> 01:16:05,277
is nothing but an accident...

1330
01:16:05,345 --> 01:16:07,210
what happens to you.

1331
01:16:07,279 --> 01:16:10,215
That sounds like
the philosophy of a drifter.

1332
01:16:10,283 --> 01:16:12,113
Yeah. Maybe.

1333
01:16:12,185 --> 01:16:14,515
Maybe I am drifting a little.

1334
01:16:14,587 --> 01:16:18,113
I can see the two of them...

1335
01:16:18,189 --> 01:16:20,180
drifting away from me...

1336
01:16:20,260 --> 01:16:22,783
and I just stand watching.

1337
01:16:22,863 --> 01:16:27,027
What would you want
to do about that?

1338
01:16:27,100 --> 01:16:29,591
Something.
I don't know what.

1339
01:16:29,667 --> 01:16:33,127
I feel like
I'm sitting on a fence.

1340
01:16:33,206 --> 01:16:36,229
They're on opposite sides
of this fence?

1341
01:16:36,309 --> 01:16:39,037
Yeah... No.

1342
01:16:39,112 --> 01:16:40,305
I don't know.

1343
01:16:40,380 --> 01:16:44,942
I see her not being able
to forgive him.

1344
01:16:46,019 --> 01:16:47,542
For what?

1345
01:16:47,621 --> 01:16:49,555
I don't know exactly.

1346
01:16:49,622 --> 01:16:52,113
Being too much like her.

1347
01:16:52,192 --> 01:16:57,220
People always think that
she and Buck are... were alike.

1348
01:16:58,331 --> 01:17:01,323
But it's really she and Conrad.

1349
01:17:01,399 --> 01:17:03,890
They were the only two...

1350
01:17:03,970 --> 01:17:06,962
that didn't cry at the funeral.

1351
01:17:07,037 --> 01:17:11,067
It's not easy for me to admit this...

1352
01:17:11,144 --> 01:17:12,609
but. Um...

1353
01:17:12,679 --> 01:17:14,145
she didn't...

1354
01:17:18,149 --> 01:17:21,676
His mother doesn't
show him much affection.

1355
01:17:21,755 --> 01:17:25,417
I'm not trying
to put her down.

1356
01:17:25,492 --> 01:17:29,019
Did she give Buck
much affection?

1357
01:17:29,095 --> 01:17:31,529
God. Yes.
She loved Buck.

1358
01:17:31,595 --> 01:17:33,564
Bucky got so much.

1359
01:17:33,631 --> 01:17:37,158
What she felt for him was special.

1360
01:17:37,237 --> 01:17:39,761
He was her first-born.

1361
01:17:39,837 --> 01:17:41,600
And you?

1362
01:17:41,675 --> 01:17:43,140
I loved Buck.

1363
01:17:43,210 --> 01:17:45,371
I mean your wife's affection.

1364
01:17:45,444 --> 01:17:46,912
For me?

1365
01:17:46,979 --> 01:17:48,277
Yes.

1366
01:17:49,381 --> 01:17:51,145
She's very...

1367
01:17:51,216 --> 01:17:55,314
No. There's no problem
with her for me.

1368
01:17:55,386 --> 01:17:59,085
We've been married
nearly 21 years.

1369
01:18:00,193 --> 01:18:01,658
Everybody loves Beth.

1370
01:18:01,728 --> 01:18:05,127
For Conrad. It's been difficult.

1371
01:18:05,198 --> 01:18:07,996
He didn't talk about that?

1372
01:18:08,068 --> 01:18:11,060
We don't know what happens here.

1373
01:18:11,136 --> 01:18:13,104
It doesn't come up.

1374
01:18:17,577 --> 01:18:20,546
I guess that's what it is.

1375
01:18:20,613 --> 01:18:22,944
It's private here. Isn't it?

1376
01:18:23,015 --> 01:18:24,448
Mm-hmm.
Very private.

1377
01:18:28,220 --> 01:18:32,157
I think I know why I came here.

1378
01:18:34,261 --> 01:18:37,594
I think I came here
to talk about myself.

1379
01:18:37,662 --> 01:18:40,426
Okay. Why don't we?

1380
01:18:46,939 --> 01:18:48,274
Hi.

1381
01:18:48,408 --> 01:18:52,345
[Car Buzzer Alarm]

1382
01:18:52,345 --> 01:18:53,310
Calvin?

1383
01:18:54,514 --> 01:18:56,377
[Buzzing Continues]

1384
01:18:56,448 --> 01:18:57,916
What's the matter?

1385
01:19:04,055 --> 01:19:06,546
This will sound strange.

1386
01:19:08,127 --> 01:19:12,121
What I'm going to say
will sound strange.

1387
01:19:12,198 --> 01:19:13,662
What happened?

1388
01:19:13,733 --> 01:19:15,166
Come inside.

