It ain't so goddamned funny!

1661
01:37:30,560 --> 01:37:31,654
Don't let go!

1662
01:37:31,729 --> 01:37:33,662
I won't. Buck!

1663
01:37:33,729 --> 01:37:35,666
Everything will be okay!

1664
01:37:38,903 --> 01:37:40,198
Hang on. Brother!

1665
01:37:40,270 --> 01:37:41,795
Don't let go!

1666
01:37:41,872 --> 01:37:43,430
Stay with me!

1667
01:37:43,506 --> 01:37:45,032
Stay with me!

1668
01:37:45,109 --> 01:37:47,908
Stay with me!

1669
01:37:52,050 --> 01:37:53,310
Oh. God!

1670
01:37:56,787 --> 01:37:58,015
Bucky!

1671
01:37:59,421 --> 01:38:00,515
Buck!

1672
01:38:01,826 --> 01:38:03,657
Buck!

1673
01:38:08,430 --> 01:38:09,421
[Berger]
Hello.

1674
01:38:09,501 --> 01:38:11,059
This is Conrad.

1675
01:38:11,136 --> 01:38:12,569
What's going on?

1676
01:38:12,636 --> 01:38:14,604
I need to see you.

1677
01:38:14,671 --> 01:38:16,139
Where are you?

1678
01:38:16,207 --> 01:38:17,765
I don't know.

1679
01:38:17,841 --> 01:38:19,274
All right.

1680
01:38:19,344 --> 01:38:21,310
Get to the office.

1681
01:38:21,377 --> 01:38:22,810
I'll meet you there.

1682
01:38:22,881 --> 01:38:24,109
Okay.

1683
01:38:28,319 --> 01:38:30,810
Good. You're here.

1684
01:38:30,889 --> 01:38:32,322
Something happened.

1685
01:38:32,390 --> 01:38:33,854
Just a minute.

1686
01:38:33,925 --> 01:38:36,393
Wait till we get inside.

1687
01:38:38,563 --> 01:38:39,493
There.

1688
01:38:41,064 --> 01:38:42,622
Shit.

1689
01:38:42,698 --> 01:38:46,395
You'd think they'd assume
there'd be emergencies.

1690
01:38:46,470 --> 01:38:48,336
Don't take it off.
Just sit down.

1691
01:38:53,077 --> 01:38:54,009
Something happened.

1692
01:38:54,078 --> 01:38:55,136
What?

1693
01:38:55,212 --> 01:38:56,612
It's...

1694
01:38:56,680 --> 01:38:58,078
It's what?

1695
01:38:58,149 --> 01:38:59,613
Oh. God!

1696
01:39:01,219 --> 01:39:02,743
I need something.

1697
01:39:02,819 --> 01:39:03,947
What?

1698
01:39:04,020 --> 01:39:05,511
It keeps coming.

1699
01:39:05,590 --> 01:39:07,488
I can't stop it!

1700
01:39:07,559 --> 01:39:09,149
Don't try.

1701
01:39:09,225 --> 01:39:11,752
Got to get off the hook.

1702
01:39:11,828 --> 01:39:13,457
For what?

1703
01:39:13,529 --> 01:39:15,590
What I did to him!

1704
01:39:15,667 --> 01:39:16,792
What?

1705
01:39:16,868 --> 01:39:19,336
It must be somebody's fault...

1706
01:39:19,404 --> 01:39:21,564
or there's no point!

1707
01:39:21,639 --> 01:39:23,630
What point? It happened!

1708
01:39:23,707 --> 01:39:26,768
Oh. No. I don't mean that.

1709
01:39:26,845 --> 01:39:28,335
It's just that...

1710
01:39:28,412 --> 01:39:30,938
Bucky. I didn't mean it.

1711
01:39:31,015 --> 01:39:33,984
Bucky, I didn't mean it.

1712
01:39:34,051 --> 01:39:35,881
Bucky!

1713
01:39:35,953 --> 01:39:36,978
It wasn't your fault.

1714
01:39:37,055 --> 01:39:39,353
You said. "Get the sail down!"

1715
01:39:39,421 --> 01:39:41,551
I couldn't! It jammed!

1716
01:39:41,626 --> 01:39:43,319
And then the halyard jammed!

1717
01:39:43,394 --> 01:39:45,328
Because the goddamned
halyard jammed!

1718
01:39:45,395 --> 01:39:48,331
Then you're sittin' here
screwing around!

1719
01:39:48,399 --> 01:39:50,127
Until it's too late!

1720
01:39:50,201 --> 01:39:53,363
And I'm supposed
to take care of it!

1721
01:39:53,438 --> 01:39:54,631
That wasn't fair.

1722
01:39:54,706 --> 01:39:57,640
No! And then
you say. "Hang on!"

1723
01:39:57,707 --> 01:39:58,801
"Hang on!"

1724
01:39:58,877 --> 01:40:00,502
Then you let go!

1725
01:40:00,578 --> 01:40:02,136
Why'd you let go?

1726
01:40:02,212 --> 01:40:03,439
I got tired!

1727
01:40:03,514 --> 01:40:06,140
Yeah? Well. Screw you. You jerk!

1728
01:40:18,630 --> 01:40:22,029
It hurts to be mad at him.

1729
01:40:22,100 --> 01:40:23,567
Yeah.

1730
01:40:25,837 --> 01:40:27,862
He just wasn't careful.

1731
01:40:27,939 --> 01:40:31,841
He didn't see how
a bad thing might happen.

1732
01:40:31,908 --> 01:40:35,676
Bad things happen even
when people are careful.

1733
01:40:35,747 --> 01:40:37,680
We should've come in...

1734
01:40:37,747 --> 01:40:40,341
when it started to look bad.

1735
01:40:40,417 --> 01:40:42,750
So you made a mistake.

1736
01:40:42,819 --> 01:40:45,118
Why did he let go?

1737
01:40:45,189 --> 01:40:46,679
Why?

1738
01:40:46,756 --> 01:40:49,818
Maybe you were stronger.

1739
01:40:49,894 --> 01:40:53,125
Did that ever occur to you?

1740
01:41:01,072 --> 01:41:04,064
How long will you
punish yourself?

1741
01:41:04,140 --> 01:41:05,268
When will you quit?

1742
01:41:05,341 --> 01:41:07,037
I'd like to.

1743
01:41:07,109 --> 01:41:08,442
Why don't you?

1744
01:41:08,511 --> 01:41:11,243
It's not that easy.

1745
01:41:17,822 --> 01:41:19,287
God...

1746
01:41:19,354 --> 01:41:21,323
I loved him.

1747
01:41:25,462 --> 01:41:27,453
I know.

1748
01:41:41,979 --> 01:41:45,176
What happened?
What started all this?

1749
01:41:45,247 --> 01:41:46,738
Karen.

1750
01:41:48,519 --> 01:41:50,817
She killed herself.

1751
01:41:50,886 --> 01:41:53,912
I just found out she's dead.

1752
01:41:53,992 --> 01:41:56,051
Jesus.

1753
01:41:56,127 --> 01:41:58,322
She was fine.

1754
01:41:58,395 --> 01:42:00,728
No. She wasn't.

1755
01:42:00,796 --> 01:42:04,287
She told me!
She said she was...

1756
01:42:04,368 --> 01:42:05,336
What?

1757
01:42:05,403 --> 01:42:08,167
She was busy and
feeling good and...

1758
01:42:08,238 --> 01:42:09,261
What?

1759
01:42:11,042 --> 01:42:12,234
What?

1760
01:42:12,310 --> 01:42:13,707
If I'd known...

1761
01:42:13,778 --> 01:42:15,268
I could've done something.

1762
01:42:15,345 --> 01:42:18,144
You're taking her on. Too?

1763
01:42:18,216 --> 01:42:19,148
No!

1764
01:42:19,216 --> 01:42:20,149
No?

1765
01:42:20,216 --> 01:42:21,685
No. I just...

1766
01:42:21,752 --> 01:42:22,685
What?

1767
01:42:22,752 --> 01:42:24,185
That isn't it.

1768
01:42:24,255 --> 01:42:27,349
I feel really bad about this.

1769
01:42:27,425 --> 01:42:30,756
Just let me feel bad about this!

1770
01:42:31,929 --> 01:42:33,225
Okay.

1771
01:42:35,533 --> 01:42:38,796
Listen. I feel
bad about it. Too.

1772
01:42:42,840 --> 01:42:45,363
Why do things
happen to people?

1773
01:42:45,443 --> 01:42:47,841
It isn't fair.

1774
01:42:47,912 --> 01:42:50,608
You're right.
It isn't fair.

1775
01:42:50,680 --> 01:42:53,081
You just do one wrong thing...

1776
01:42:53,149 --> 01:42:54,618
and...

1777
01:42:54,685 --> 01:42:57,279
Um-hmm.

1778
01:42:57,354 --> 01:43:01,189
And what was the one
wrong thing you did?

1779
01:43:08,162 --> 01:43:09,631
You know.

1780
01:43:22,645 --> 01:43:24,408
You know.

1781
01:43:27,417 --> 01:43:29,318
I hung on.

1782
01:43:29,386 --> 01:43:32,514
I stayed with the boat.

1783
01:43:32,590 --> 01:43:34,216
Exactly.

1784
01:43:39,930 --> 01:43:43,921
Now. You can live
with that. Can't you?

1785
01:43:50,073 --> 01:43:52,042
I'm scared!

1786
01:43:52,109 --> 01:43:54,304
I'm scared.

1787
01:43:54,377 --> 01:43:56,608
Feelings are scary.

1788
01:43:56,680 --> 01:43:58,773
And sometimes they're painful.

1789
01:43:58,849 --> 01:44:01,113
If you can't feel pain...

1790
01:44:01,185 --> 01:44:04,176
you won't feel
anything else.

1791
01:44:04,255 --> 01:44:06,849
You know what I'm saying?

1792
01:44:09,960 --> 01:44:11,518
I think so.

1793
01:44:14,465 --> 01:44:16,194
You're here. You're alive.

1794
01:44:16,265 --> 01:44:19,064
Don't say you don't feel that.

1795
01:44:19,136 --> 01:44:21,363
It doesn't feel good.

1796
01:44:21,438 --> 01:44:22,871
It is good.

1797
01:44:22,939 --> 01:44:24,407
Believe me.

1798
01:44:28,813 --> 01:44:30,676
How do you know?

1799
01:44:32,750 --> 01:44:34,944
Because I'm your friend.

1800
01:44:39,256 --> 01:44:42,692
I don't know
what I would've done...

1801
01:44:42,760 --> 01:44:45,194
if you hadn't been here.

1802
01:44:48,765 --> 01:44:51,496
You're really my friend?

1803
01:44:53,604 --> 01:44:56,402
I am. Count on it.

1804
01:45:49,158 --> 01:45:50,591
Hi.

1805
01:45:50,661 --> 01:45:52,094
I would've called...

1806
01:45:52,162 --> 01:45:55,095
but I didn't
want to wake anyone.

1807
01:45:55,162 --> 01:45:56,595
About the other night...

1808
01:45:56,667 --> 01:45:59,100
I liked being with you.

1809
01:45:59,167 --> 01:46:01,603
I didn't like myself.

1810
01:46:01,671 --> 01:46:03,604
Conrad. I was stupid.

1811
01:46:03,671 --> 01:46:06,609
That was dumb of me to laugh.

1812
01:46:06,676 --> 01:46:08,609
It was my fault.

1813
01:46:08,679 --> 01:46:10,703
I was embarrassed.

1814
01:46:10,779 --> 01:46:11,939
Really?

1815
01:46:12,015 --> 01:46:13,779
You were embarrassed?

1816
01:46:13,850 --> 01:46:16,081
When those boys came in...

1817
01:46:16,153 --> 01:46:18,644
it was awful and awkward.

1818
01:46:18,720 --> 01:46:20,984
When I'm embarrassed. I laugh.

1819
01:46:21,055 --> 01:46:24,354
They were just having
a good time.

1820
01:46:24,426 --> 01:46:28,386
I let them interfere
with what was happening.

1821
01:46:28,465 --> 01:46:29,930
It was dumb.

1822
01:46:30,000 --> 01:46:33,527
I've done lots of
dumb things lately.

1823
01:46:33,604 --> 01:46:38,301
I just didn't know if you were
being straight with me.

1824
01:46:41,444 --> 01:46:42,912
Yeah?

1825
01:46:42,979 --> 01:46:46,345
Anyway. I'd like
to try it again.

1826
01:46:46,417 --> 01:46:47,850
It worked okay...

1827
01:46:47,917 --> 01:46:50,045
except for the bowling.

1828
01:46:50,118 --> 01:46:51,587
Yes.

1829
01:46:51,654 --> 01:46:53,520
Yes?

1830
01:46:54,625 --> 01:46:56,684
Yes.

1831
01:46:57,761 --> 01:47:00,252
Are you going to school?

1832
01:47:00,331 --> 01:47:03,162
No. Not on Sunday.

1833
01:47:06,002 --> 01:47:07,993
Have you eaten?

1834
01:47:08,072 --> 01:47:10,095
No. I haven't.

1835
01:47:10,171 --> 01:47:12,608
Do you want some breakfast?

1836
01:47:14,545 --> 01:47:16,011
Okay.

1837
01:47:29,760 --> 01:47:31,055
Mom!

1838
01:47:32,930 --> 01:47:35,296
All right.
How about that?

1839
01:47:35,363 --> 01:47:36,796
Boy. Oh. Boy.

1840
01:47:36,867 --> 01:47:38,835
I do love that.

1841
01:47:38,902 --> 01:47:41,894
These holes sure do love you.

1842
01:47:41,970 --> 01:47:45,965
We should spend more time
playing golf together.

1843
01:47:46,042 --> 01:47:49,011
Maybe our next vacation...
strictly golf.

1844
01:47:49,078 --> 01:47:50,546
Pinehurst.
Myrtle Beach.

1845
01:47:50,613 --> 01:47:52,582
Pinehurst would be nice.

1846
01:47:52,649 --> 01:47:55,640
I think Connie would
like Pinehurst.

1847
01:47:55,719 --> 01:47:59,176
Is that deliberate
or just a reflex?

1848
01:47:59,256 --> 01:48:02,247
I assumed you meant him. Too.

1849
01:48:02,326 --> 01:48:05,295
I'm surprised you
haven't called him.

1850
01:48:05,362 --> 01:48:07,328
I'll call him tonight.

1851
01:48:07,398 --> 01:48:10,390
Can we have a little drink?

1852
01:48:10,466 --> 01:48:12,435
Drink. Yes. Little. No.

1853
01:48:12,502 --> 01:48:13,970
Let's finish this.

1854
01:48:14,037 --> 01:48:14,970
What?

1855
01:48:15,037 --> 01:48:16,506
What you started.

1856
01:48:16,573 --> 01:48:18,541
Me? There's no point.

1857
01:48:18,609 --> 01:48:20,076
He controls you.

1858
01:48:20,144 --> 01:48:22,112
He isn't the problem.

1859
01:48:22,179 --> 01:48:23,645
Isn't he?

1860
01:48:23,712 --> 01:48:27,113
No. Let's talk about
what's bothering you.

1861
01:48:27,184 --> 01:48:30,176
No. Let's discuss
what's bothering you.

1862
01:48:30,252 --> 01:48:34,247
How did I make you
so angry with me?

1863
01:48:34,323 --> 01:48:36,792
You blame me
for everything.

1864
01:48:36,859 --> 01:48:39,328
Can't you see
beyond yourself?

1865
01:48:39,395 --> 01:48:40,863
No. I can't!

1866
01:48:40,930 --> 01:48:43,921
Neither can you
or anybody else!

1867
01:48:44,001 --> 01:48:45,434
I'm just honest.

1868
01:48:45,502 --> 01:48:46,969
Stop being honest...

1869
01:48:47,037 --> 01:48:49,005
and start being generous!

1870
01:48:49,073 --> 01:48:50,537
Think about him!

1871
01:48:50,604 --> 01:48:53,576
What does he expect from me?

1872
01:48:53,644 --> 01:48:57,636
He wants a hug
when he passes exams?

1873
01:48:57,712 --> 01:49:00,706
I can't respond
when someone says...

1874
01:49:00,783 --> 01:49:03,752
"I did something
great. Love me."

1875
01:49:03,819 --> 01:49:07,814
He wants to know
you don't hate him.

1876
01:49:07,890 --> 01:49:10,381
Mothers don't hate their sons.

1877
01:49:10,461 --> 01:49:13,430
Is that what he told you?

1878
01:49:13,497 --> 01:49:17,488
You accept what he says
with no questions.

1879
01:49:17,568 --> 01:49:20,560
I'm trying to
keep this family...

1880
01:49:20,636 --> 01:49:23,604
What does everyone
want from me?

1881
01:49:23,671 --> 01:49:28,109
Listen. We all just
want you to be happy.

1882
01:49:28,176 --> 01:49:29,645
Happy?

1883
01:49:29,712 --> 01:49:30,680
Yes.

1884
01:49:30,747 --> 01:49:34,444
You tell me
the definition of happy.

1885
01:49:34,518 --> 01:49:37,783
First. Be sure your kids are safe...

1886
01:49:37,854 --> 01:49:41,345
that nobody's been hit by a car...

1887
01:49:41,425 --> 01:49:44,417
or drowned in your swimming pool!

1888
01:49:44,493 --> 01:49:47,987
Then tell me how to be happy!

1889
01:50:41,518 --> 01:50:43,984
I'm turning in.

1890
01:50:44,054 --> 01:50:45,520
Dinner was good.

1891
01:50:45,587 --> 01:50:47,055
Really good.

1892
01:50:47,122 --> 01:50:49,555
It's early. You tired?

1893
01:50:49,626 --> 01:50:51,890
It was a rough week.

1894
01:50:51,962 --> 01:50:55,693
Your grandmother
wasn't too tough on you?

1895
01:50:55,765 --> 01:50:57,734
No. She was fine.

1896
01:51:00,304 --> 01:51:02,828
I'm glad you're back.

1897
01:51:17,185 --> 01:51:18,654
Good night.

1898
01:52:37,434 --> 01:52:41,837
[Sobbing]

1899
01:52:48,578 --> 01:52:50,011
Calvin?

1900
01:53:01,957 --> 01:53:03,859
Why are you crying?

1901
01:53:10,701 --> 01:53:12,167
Can I. Uh...

1902
01:53:12,234 --> 01:53:14,703
Can I get you something?

1903
01:53:16,805 --> 01:53:18,274
I don't...

1904
01:53:18,341 --> 01:53:20,310
What did you say?

1905
01:53:24,479 --> 01:53:26,779
Calvin. What did you say?

1906
01:53:26,850 --> 01:53:28,372
[Sighing]

1907
01:53:31,319 --> 01:53:33,515
Tell me.

1908
01:53:40,162 --> 01:53:41,631
You are beautiful.

1909
01:53:45,234 --> 01:53:47,725
And you are unpredictable.

1910
01:53:49,840 --> 01:53:51,805
But you're so cautious.

1911
01:53:54,411 --> 01:53:55,844
You're determined. Beth...

1912
01:53:55,912 --> 01:53:58,037
but you know something?

1913
01:54:00,350 --> 01:54:01,942
You're not strong.

1914
01:54:04,054 --> 01:54:07,319
I don't know
if you're really giving.

1915
01:54:10,493 --> 01:54:11,984
Tell me something.

1916
01:54:12,060 --> 01:54:14,154
Do you love me?

1917
01:54:16,265 --> 01:54:18,734
Do you really love me?

1918
01:54:21,104 --> 01:54:24,939
I feel the way I've always
felt about you.

1919
01:54:37,554 --> 01:54:40,020
We would've been all right...

1920
01:54:40,090 --> 01:54:43,582
if there hadn't been any mess.

1921
01:54:45,194 --> 01:54:47,662
But you can't handle mess.

1922
01:54:49,265 --> 01:54:52,724
You need everything neat and easy.

1923
01:54:53,837 --> 01:54:55,304
I don't know.

1924
01:54:55,372 --> 01:54:57,840
Maybe you can't love anybody.

1925
01:54:57,908 --> 01:55:00,376
It was so much Buck.

1926
01:55:00,444 --> 01:55:05,438
It's as if you buried
all your love with him.

1927
01:55:05,515 --> 01:55:07,484
I don't understand that.

1928
01:55:09,086 --> 01:55:12,578
Maybe it wasn't even Buck.

1929
01:55:12,654 --> 01:55:15,055
Maybe it was just you.

1930
01:55:15,125 --> 01:55:20,756
Maybe, finally, it was
the best of you that you buried.

1931
01:55:23,332 --> 01:55:25,301
But whatever it was...

1932
01:55:28,939 --> 01:55:31,908
I don't know who you are.

1933
01:55:31,975 --> 01:55:36,469
I don't know what
we've been playing at.

1934
01:55:39,082 --> 01:55:41,207
So I was crying.

1935
01:55:45,720 --> 01:55:49,783
Because I don't know
if I love you anymore.

1936
01:55:52,828 --> 01:55:57,323
And I don't know
what I'll do without that.

1937
01:57:27,090 --> 01:57:28,020
[Door Slams]

1938
01:58:28,585 --> 01:58:29,676
Dad?

1939
01:58:32,921 --> 01:58:35,912
The yard looks smaller
without leaves.

1940
01:58:37,493 --> 01:58:38,961
Dad. What happened?

1941
01:58:41,064 --> 01:58:44,555
Your mother's
going away for a while.

1942
01:58:44,634 --> 01:58:45,792
Where?

1943
01:58:45,868 --> 01:58:47,095
Why?

1944
01:58:47,170 --> 01:58:48,636
Back to Houston.

1945
01:58:49,706 --> 01:58:51,171
I don't know.

1946
01:58:52,274 --> 01:58:53,707
Why? What...

1947
01:58:55,810 --> 01:58:57,279
I know why.

1948
01:58:57,345 --> 01:58:59,314
It's me. Isn't it?

1949
01:58:59,381 --> 01:59:00,350
No.

1950
01:59:00,417 --> 01:59:01,850
It's my fault.

1951
01:59:01,917 --> 01:59:04,180
Don't do that to yourself!

1952
01:59:04,252 --> 01:59:05,685
It's nobody's fault!

1953
01:59:05,756 --> 01:59:09,157
Things happen.
People don't always have answers.

1954
01:59:12,962 --> 01:59:16,761
I don't know why
I'm yelling at you.

1955
01:59:16,832 --> 01:59:19,926
You should do
that more often.

1956
01:59:20,002 --> 01:59:21,729
Haul my ass a little.

1957
01:59:21,805 --> 01:59:23,238
Get after me.

1958
01:59:25,573 --> 01:59:27,411
Like you did for him.

1959
01:59:27,542 --> 01:59:29,011
He needed it.

1960
01:59:29,078 --> 01:59:30,011
You didn't.

1961
01:59:30,078 --> 01:59:33,015
You were always
so hard on yourself.

1962
01:59:33,082 --> 01:59:35,412
I never had the heart.

1963
01:59:35,484 --> 01:59:38,010
Oh. Dad. Don't.

1964
01:59:38,087 --> 01:59:40,318
Well. It's the truth.

1965
01:59:42,091 --> 01:59:44,524
I never worried about you.

1966
01:59:44,594 --> 01:59:47,529
I just wasn't listening.

1967
01:59:48,662 --> 01:59:50,895
I wasn't sending
many signals then.

1968
01:59:50,966 --> 01:59:52,867
You couldn't do anything.

1969
01:59:52,935 --> 01:59:56,497
I should've got
a handle on it somehow.

1970
02:00:01,609 --> 02:00:05,546
I used to figure you had
a handle for everything.

1971
02:00:05,613 --> 02:00:07,845
You knew it all.

1972
02:00:07,917 --> 02:00:11,911
You always made us feel
everything would be all right.

1973
02:00:12,988 --> 02:00:15,957
I've thought about that
a lot lately.

1974
02:00:16,024 --> 02:00:18,493
I really admire you for it.

1975
02:00:18,560 --> 02:00:20,551
Don't admire people too much.

1976
02:00:20,630 --> 02:00:23,724
They'll disappoint you sometimes.

1977
02:00:24,868 --> 02:00:26,733
I'm not disappointed.

1978
02:00:29,904 --> 02:00:32,475
I love you.

1979
02:00:38,081 --> 02:00:39,514
I love you. Too.

1980
